I posted this in the <#C2YH119N2|hubl> channel last night, but perhaps someone here can help a brotha out. :slightly_smiling_face:

Has anyone had any luck or know if it’s possible to use a {{ printed_field }} inside of a conditional statement within a loop  {% for %}.  This is my code block:

```{% for item in module.menu.translated_menus %}
         {% if (content.slug is string_startingwith "{{ item.lang_url }}/") or (content.slug =="fr") %}
           {% menu id="{{ item.menu_translated }}" %}
         {% endif %}
   {% endfor %}```

The {{ item.lang_url }} doesn’t seem to want to print so that the logic works.  Am I doing something wrong or is this not possible?

Thanks guys.  Any help is massively appreciated.

I believe that you said yesterday you had a parsing error when you removed the braces and quotes.

I have a feeling the issue is likely the `/` after `item.lang_url`

give this a shot:

```{% for item in module.menu.translated_menus %}
         {% if content.slug is string_startingwith item.lang_url  || content.slug =="fr" %}
           {% menu id=item.menu_translated  %}
         {% endif %}
   {% endfor %}```
